# Claude project skills

Before answering or editing anything tied to **this repo’s Archbee docs**, **`archbee.json`**, or **`docs/`** (folders **BASIC/**, **MEDIA/**, **DEVELOPER/**):

1. Read **`.claude/skills/archbee-docs-space/SKILL.md`** (navigation rules, naming, quality checks).
2. Read **`.claude/skills/archbee-docs-space/reference-blocks.md`** — start with **GitHub sync — canonical patterns** (TeX, Mermaid, Changelog, Map, image, YouTube), then block templates, Imgur URLs, slugs.

If other folders exist under **`.claude/skills/`**, read each relevant **`SKILL.md`** (YAML `description` tells you when it applies) before work that matches that skill.

Do not invent block fences or `archbee.json` structure from memory when these files define the canonical patterns for this project.
